<div id="review_1127276177" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1127276177" />
    <a title="Natasha Polis" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/19208239-natasha-polis"><img alt="Natasha Polis" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1445474659p2/19208239.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1127276177?book_show_action=true">Dec 09, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Natasha Polis" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Natasha Polis" href="/user/show/19208239-natasha-polis">Natasha Polis</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1127276177" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16678074445417289799">I finished this book in 12 hours. ONE DAY. I finished it in one day. I&apos;m giving it 5 stars because I still can&apos;t believe that I, Natasha Polis, finished a book in a day. I&apos;ve never done that before. Ever. It was so good and so entertaining. Lots of sexytimes, very mature scenes, which I did enjoy but still not heavily detailed which I&apos;m very thankful for. The emotions and tears I felt for and had for Miles really made this book. I can&apos;t wait to read another Colleen Hoover book!</span>
  <span id="freeText16678074445417289799" style="display:none">I finished this book in 12 hours. ONE DAY. I finished it in one day. I'm giving it 5 stars because I still can't believe that I, Natasha Polis, finished a book in a day. I've never done that before. Ever. It was so good and so entertaining. Lots of sexytimes, very mature scenes, which I did enjoy but still not heavily detailed which I'm very thankful for. The emotions and tears I felt for and had for Miles really made this book. I can't wait to read another Colleen Hoover book!</span>
